#. type: Title ==
#: source/upgrading/topics/migrate_themes.adoc:3
#, no-wrap
msgid "Migrating Themes"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/upgrading/topics/migrate_themes.adoc:7
#, no-wrap
msgid "If you have created any custom themes they must be migrated to the new server. Any changes to the built-in themes might\n"
"need to be reflected in your custom themes, depending on which aspects you have customized.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/upgrading/topics/migrate_themes.adoc:10
#, no-wrap
msgid "You must copy your custom themes from the old server “themes” directory to the new server “themes” directory.\n"
"After that you need to review the changes below and consider if the changes need to be applied to your custom theme.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/upgrading/topics/migrate_themes.adoc:12
#, no-wrap
msgid "In summary:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/upgrading/topics/migrate_themes.adoc:15
#, no-wrap
msgid "If you have customized any of the changed templates listed below you need to compare the template from the base theme\n"
"to see if there are changes you need to apply.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/upgrading/topics/migrate_themes.adoc:17
#, no-wrap
msgid "If you have customized any of the styles and are extending the {project_name} themes you need to review the changes to\n"
"the styles. If you are extending the base theme you can skip this step.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/upgrading/topics/migrate_themes.adoc:18
#, no-wrap
msgid "If you have customized messages you might need to change the key or value or to add additional messages.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/upgrading/topics/migrate_themes.adoc:21
#, no-wrap
msgid "ifeval::[{project_product}==true]\n"
"Each step is described in more detail below the list of changes.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/upgrading/topics/migrate_themes.adoc:24
#, no-wrap
msgid "include::rhsso/migrate_themes-changes-71.adoc[leveloffset=0]\n"
"endif::[]\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: source/upgrading/topics/migrate_themes.adoc:25
#, no-wrap
msgid "Migrating Templates"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/upgrading/topics/migrate_themes.adoc:30
#, no-wrap
msgid "If you have customized any of the templates you need to carefully review the changes that have been made to the templates\n"
"to decide if you need to apply these changes to your customized templates. Most likely you will need to apply the same\n"
"changes to your customized templates. If you have not customized any of the listed templates you can skip this section.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/upgrading/topics/migrate_themes.adoc:35
#, no-wrap
msgid "A best practice is to use a diff tool to compare the templates to see what changes you might need to make to your\n"
"customized template. If you have only made minor changes it is simpler to compare the updated template to your\n"
"customized template. However, if you have made many changes it might be easier to compare the new template to your\n"
"customized old template, as this will show you what changes you need to make.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/upgrading/topics/migrate_themes.adoc:37
#, no-wrap
msgid "The following screenshot compares the info.ftl template from the Login theme and an example custom theme:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Block title
#: source/upgrading/topics/migrate_themes.adoc:38
#, no-wrap
msgid "Comparison of the updated version of a Login theme template with an example custom Login theme template"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/upgrading/topics/migrate_themes.adoc:40
#, no-wrap
msgid "image:images/theme-migration-meld-info-1.png[]\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/upgrading/topics/migrate_themes.adoc:44
#, no-wrap
msgid "From this comparison it is easy to identify that the first change (“Hello world!!”) was a customization, while the\n"
"second change (“if pageRedirectUri”) is a change to the base theme. By copying the second change to your custom template,\n"
"you have successfully updated your customized template.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/upgrading/topics/migrate_themes.adoc:47
#, no-wrap
msgid "For the alternative approach the following screenshot compares the info.ftl template from the old installation with\n"
"the updated info.ftl template from the new installation:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Block title
#: source/upgrading/topics/migrate_themes.adoc:48
#, no-wrap
msgid "Comparison of an example custom Login theme template with the updated version of the Login theme template"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/upgrading/topics/migrate_themes.adoc:50
#, no-wrap
msgid "image:images/theme-migration-meld-info-2.png[]\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/upgrading/topics/migrate_themes.adoc:54
#, no-wrap
msgid "From this comparison it is easy to identify what has been changed in the base template. You will then manually have to\n"
"make the same changes to your modified template. Since this approach is not as simple as the first approach, only use\n"
"this approach if the first one is not feasible.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: source/upgrading/topics/migrate_themes.adoc:55
#, no-wrap
msgid "Migrating Messages"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/upgrading/topics/migrate_themes.adoc:60
#, no-wrap
msgid "If you have added support for another language, you need to apply all the changes listed above. If you have not added\n"
"support for another language, you might not need to change anything; you only have to make changes if you have changed\n"
"an affected message in your theme.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/upgrading/topics/migrate_themes.adoc:62
#, no-wrap
msgid "For added values, review the value of the message in the base theme to determine if you need to customize that message.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/upgrading/topics/migrate_themes.adoc:64
#, no-wrap
msgid "For renamed keys, rename the key in your custom theme.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/upgrading/topics/migrate_themes.adoc:66
#, no-wrap
msgid "For changed values, check the value in the base theme to determine if you need to make changes to your custom theme.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: source/upgrading/topics/migrate_themes.adoc:67
#, no-wrap
msgid "Migrating Styles"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/upgrading/topics/migrate_themes.adoc:71
#, no-wrap
msgid "If you are inheriting styles from the keycloak or rh-sso themes you might need to update your custom styles to reflect\n"
"changes made to the styles from the built-in themes.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/upgrading/topics/migrate_themes.adoc:74
#, no-wrap
msgid "A best practice is to use a diff tool to compare the changes to stylesheets between the old server installation and the\n"
"new server installation.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/upgrading/topics/migrate_themes.adoc:76
#, no-wrap
msgid "For example, using the diff command:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/upgrading/topics/migrate_themes.adoc:78
#, no-wrap
msgid "[source,bash,subs=+attributes]\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: source/upgrading/topics/migrate_themes.adoc:81
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ diff {project_dirref}_OLD/themes/keycloak/login/resources/css/login.css \\\n"
"{project_dirref}_NEW/themes/keycloak/login/resources/css/login.css\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/upgrading/topics/migrate_themes.adoc:84
#, no-wrap
msgid "Review the changes and determine if they affect your custom styling.\n"
msgstr ""

